{"key":"processedPost-7108344","value":{"id":7108344,"first":7051427,"last":7254458,"when":1183163159,"utime":"06/30/07 03:25 AM","content":"The difference between a boiling kettle of water and an oven is that the steam provides a 100% humidity environment, which an oven does not.  Thus, your substrate does not lose moisture when surrounded by steam.  If you want to sterilize in an oven, put your substate in a jar without holes in the lid and set the oven to 225F.  Hopefully, your jar can withstand the pressure created and not explode.<br />RR","title":"Re: Mr. Roger says won't you be my Shroomy neighbor?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}